    <h3 style="text-align: left;"><span>Welcome</span></h3>


    <div class="text clearfix">
      <p><i><b>Welcome to 2014-2015&nbsp;Tryout Sign-up for Campton United Soccer Club</b></i><br />
<br />
<b>Tryout Process:</b></p>

<ul>
	<li>Players MUST sign-up within this system prior to tryout</li>
	<li>It is highly recommended that players attend all tryout dates/times for their age group to assure the best evaluation.</li>
	<li>All players must wear shin guards &amp; soccer shoes and bring water and soccer ball</li>
	<li>Please plan to arrive 30 minutes prior to tryout time to check-in at the main building (concession stand area) at James O&#39;Breen Park.</li>
	<li>Each player will be notified of club offering&nbsp;via email ONLY following tryouts.</li>
</ul>

<p><br />
<u><b>Why Campton?</b></u><br />
<br />
<b>Professional Coaching</b><br />
At <b>Campton United</b>, our <b>professional coaching staff</b> is responsible for all facets of our player development and programming.&nbsp; Our Directors use over 40 years of coaching experience at all levels of the game. Each staff member continues to raise their development by attending USSF National Level Coaching Licenses to accelerate&nbsp;the development path for players age 4 to 18 years old. Many of our staff members have coached in NCAA Division 1, Division II, Division III and Junior College Programs.<br />
<br />
<b>Player Development Curriculum</b><br />
The Directors of Coaching have&nbsp;a club wide curriculum model that meets the demands of developing all players to their potential. Using the models set forth by US Soccer and US Club Soccer, our curriculum is highlighted by valuing skills like: ball mastery, possession, and one on one abilities. We also provide more guidance than direction in teaching our players in tactical situations. It&#39;s a player&#39;s game, not a coach&#39;s game and we truly value that at Campton United. Regardless of age or level, the club curriculum guides all our teams&#39; development.<br />
<br />
<b>Facilities</b><br />
Another value to playing for Campton United is access to top training and playing facilities.&nbsp; Our club opened its very own, 22,000 sq. ft. Indoor Training Facility in December of 2010 at the corner of Dean and Peck in St. Charles, IL.&nbsp; Having this indoor facility along with exclusive training fields, our players enjoy more training opportunities than any other local club.&nbsp; This combination gives our players access to training 12 months of the year if they choose.<br />
<br />
<b>Soccer Value</b><br />
No one puts more time into soccer development.&nbsp; Our players will see between 130 and 190 hours of training instruction and between 30 and 50 competitive games through leagues and tournaments.&nbsp; There is never an extra cost to do more training or to get winter skills training.&nbsp; When packaged with our <b>professional staff, facilities and curriculum</b>, it is no wonder our teams regularly play in the highest leagues and divisions available in the area.</p>

<p><b>For all questions about our tryouts please visit</b><br />
<br />
<a href="http://www.camptonunited.com/page/show/461132-locations-and-times" target="_blank">http://www.camptonunited.com/page/show/461132-locations-and-times</a></p>

